##Wuhan "three sisters in shelter" , all discharged from hospital

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Wu Yi, correspondent, Zhang Yang, Liu Wenqin

On the afternoon of March 4, five new pneumonia patients were discharged from the east side of the 7th floor of the Wuhan Union Hospital. Thepaper.cn learned from the National Sun Yat-sen University Sun Yat-sen Memorial Hospital that the hospital's second batch of Hubei Epidemic Prevention and control medical team has treated and discharged 15 people since it took over the eastern district of the 7th floor of the ICU on February 8, in addition, some patients were transferred to hospital after their condition became mild.

Medical team leader, Deputy Secretary of the Hospital Party Committee and Vice Dean Professor Xu Kewei, said the five patients discharged the oldest 66-year-old, the youngest 33 years old. After anti-virus, Chinese Patent Medicine and support treatment, the body temperature returned to normal for more than 3 days, the respiratory symptoms improved significantly, the lung CT showed obvious inflammation absorption, two consecutive negative respiratory tract pathogens nucleic acid test, to cure discharged from hospital standard.

It is understood that March 4 discharged from the hospital in the five recovered patients, there are three medical staff known as the "three sisters shelter. ". At that time, the seven-floor East Ward was an emergency newly opened critical care ward to relieve the shortage of critical beds. The "three sisters in the shelter" were transferred from the Kong Hon Shelter Hospital in the early hours of February 9 due to their serious condition, after that, they were in beds 81,82,83, all in the same room.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
When the hospital, "shelter three sisters" and medical staff photo. National Sun Yat-sen University Sun Yat-sen Memorial Hospital

At the Shelter Hospital, the "three sisters" were in a similar situation. They all had a high fever and at one point the Oxygenation dropped to 85 percent. "At 85% , the Oxygenation can go into respiratory failure, which is dangerous. After entering the ward, we immediately carried out comprehensive treatment programs such as oxygen therapy, antiviral therapy, improved nutrition, integrated Chinese and Western medicine treatment, and the Oxygenation of all three quickly reached over 95% . The treatment effect was very good,"said Zhou Minggen, ward director, after more than 10 days of comprehensive treatment, three people have stopped oxygen, temperature gradually returned to normal, and finally reached the discharge standard.

At the time of discharge, the "three sisters" wrote messages on the wish wall made by the nurses in the ward to cheer for the medical team and other patients. "The clouds will clear, take off the mask tomorrow will not be far, come on, "we are all heroes, "go home early and reunite with family" ..
